amd - Approximate minimum degree reorderings
        http://www.cise.ufl.edu/research/sparse/amd/
blaslike - Routines from BLAS modified by Matthias Bollhoefer
fortran - ILUPACK specific
metis - Metis 4.0/ SCOTCH 5.x provides a wrapper to be used like Metis 
        http://glaros.dtc.umn.edu/gkhome/views/metis        
        http://www.labri.fr/perso/pelegrin/scotch/
mumps - a MUltifrontal Massively Parallel sparse direct Solver
        http://graal.ens-lyon.fr/MUMPS/
sparskit - A basic tool-kit for sparse matrix computations
        http://www-users.cs.umn.edu/~saad/software/SPARSKIT/sparskit.html
sparspack - The Waterloo Sparse Matrix Package
        http://www.cs.uwaterloo.ca/~jageorge/Sparspak/sparspak.html

The blas, lapack and metis libs can be used from NACSDEPS.
Mumps source is only available in ilupack package not from internet.
It should be compiled into ilupack for the moment.
AMD can be downloaded from the internet. It obviously has not been modified
much by Matthias Bollhöfer.
Everything else should be used from ilupack.
